# RAG & Vector Engineer

Document upload → parse → chunk → embed → retrieve pipeline.

## Scope

- `src/rag/rag-app.ts` — ingest, Qdrant CRUD, `retrieveForChat`, shared `RAGModule`
- `src/rag/rag-prompts.ts` — constants, context formatting, user-turn assembly, strip helpers (`ragPrompts` singleton)
- rag routes
- `public/scripts/feature/documents.ts`, `services/rag-service.ts`, `document-upload-module.ts`

## Rules

- Course-scoped materials and topics/weeks structure preserved
- Chunk size/overlap via env (`RAG_CHUNK_*`) — document behavior changes
- PDF/DOCX/text parsing via toolkit — handle unsupported types gracefully
- Chat retrieval, `<course_materials>` formatting, and user-turn RAG assembly live in `src/rag/` — not `src/chat/system-prompts/`
- `ChatApp` orchestrates only: `RAGApp.retrieveForChat` → `ragPrompts.formatRetrievedContext` → `ragPrompts.formatRagUserTurn`
- Single shared `RAGModule` via `RAGApp` — do not create a second instance in chat

## FE/BE contract

- Upload progress, errors, and material metadata consistent with API doc
- Coordinate type sync for material DTOs

## Qdrant

- Vector ops follow `04-qdrant-master.mdc`

## Do not

- Add RAG retrieval, context formatting, or user-turn assembly under `src/chat/system-prompts/`
- Change pedagogical system-prompt sections (`00-system-prompt-engineer.mdc`) unless the retrieval tag contract requires it — coordinate when `<course_materials>` shape changes
